        "id": "idpKX136kp",
        "name": "Facebook",
        "domain": "facebook.com",
        "claimed": false,
        "description": "Our mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together.",
        "longDescription": "Facebook is a social networking platform founded by Mark Zuckerberg in February 2004. It is headquartered in Menlo Park, California, United States. The company began as a project called Facemash by Zuckerberg while he was still a student at Harvard University. It quickly evolved into Thefacebook and was initially limited to Harvard students before expanding to other universities and finally becoming available to anyone over the age of 13 with a valid email address. Facebook's headquarters, known as Facebook Campus, is located in Menlo Park, California. The campus spans over 430,000 square feet and consists of several buildings designed to foster innovation and collaboration amongst employees. The main building, called MPK20, features an open floor plan with multiple workspaces, cafes, and outdoor spaces. The campus also includes amenities such as a fitness center, dining facilities, and even a bike repair shop. The main product offered by Facebook is its social networking platform, where users can create profiles, connect with friends and family, share photos and videos, and interact with content posted by others. Additionally, Facebook owns several other popular services, including Instagram, WhatsApp, and Oculus VR. Facebook operates on a global scale, with users from all around the world. As of 2021, Facebook has over 2.8 billion monthly active users. The company has also acquired several noteworthy subsidiaries and made strategic partnerships. Instagram and WhatsApp are the most notable subsidiaries, both of which have become integral parts of the Facebook ecosystem. In terms of market position, Facebook is one of the dominant players in the global technology industry. It competes with other social media platforms such as Twitter and Snapchat but maintains a significant lead in terms of user base and market share. Facebook's global sales primarily come from advertising revenue generated through its platforms. Throughout its history, Facebook has undergone many significant events, achievements, and changes. Some notable milestones include going public in 2012, surpassing one billion users in 2012, and acquiring Instagram for $1 billion in 2012. Currently, Facebook continues to evolve and adapt to the ever-changing digital landscape. The company is focusing on privacy and security enhancements, content moderation, and expanding its presence in emerging markets. Facebook's latest updates include the integration of messaging services across its platforms and the introduction of cryptocurrency-based payment systems. In conclusion, Facebook is a global social networking platform that offers a range of products and services. With its headquarters in Menlo Park, California, the company has established itself as a leader in the industry. Facebook's dominance in terms of user base and market share, along with its strategic acquisitions and partnerships, contributes to its strong market position. The company continues to grow and adapt to meet the demands of its users and the digital landscape.",
